===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ls` baraye namayesh-e list-e file-ha va directory-ha (pooshe-ha) dar mahall-e konuni (current location) estefade mishavad. Be zabane sade, yani file-ha va pooshe-hayi ke dar oonja hastand ro neshun mide.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `ls -l`  --> 📜 Namayesh-e etela'at-e bishtar (permission-ha, tedad-e link-ha, owner, size, tarikhe sakht) be surat-e list-e tafsili.
    🔹 `ls -a`  --> 👀 Namayesh-e hame-ye file-ha, hata file-haye makhfi (file-hayi ke ba "." shoru mishavand).
    🔹 `ls -t`  --> ⏱️ Moratab sazi bar asase tarikhe akharin taghir.
    🔹 `ls -h`  --> 📏 Namayesh-e size-e file-ha be surate ghabele khandan baraye ensan (human-readable: K, M, G).
    🔹 `ls -R`  --> 🔄️ Namayesh-e recursive-e directory-ha va file-haye dakhele anha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ls

    🔹 List-e sadeye file-ha va directory-ha dar mahall-e konuni.

    $ ls -l

    🔹 Namayesh-e etela'at-e kamel dar morede file-ha va directory-ha.

    $ ls -a

    🔹 Namayesh-e hame-ye file-ha, hata file-haye makhfi ke ba "." shoru mishavand.

    $ ls -lah

    🔹 Combination-i az option-haye -l, -a, va -h: etela'at-e kamel, hameye file-ha, va size-ha be surate ghabele khandan.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ls -lt

    🔹 List-e file-ha va pooshe-ha ba etela'ate kamel, moratab shode bar asase tarikhe akharin dastkari (modification). Akharin file-e dastkari shode dar aval neshan dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ls` command is used to list files and directories in the current location. Simply put, it shows the files and folders present in that directory.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `ls -l`  --> 📜 Show more detailed information (permissions, number of links, owner, size, modification date) in a long listing format.
    🔹 `ls -a`  --> 👀 Show all files, including hidden files (files that start with ".").
    🔹 `ls -t`  --> ⏱️ Sort by modification time (most recently modified first).
    🔹 `ls -h`  --> 📏 Display file sizes in a human-readable format (K, M, G).
    🔹 `ls -R`  --> 🔄️ Recursively list subdirectories encountered.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ls

    🔹 Simple list of files and directories in the current directory.

    $ ls -l

    🔹 Display complete information about files and directories.

    $ ls -a

    🔹 Display all files, even hidden ones that start with ".".

    $ ls -lah

    🔹 Combination of -l, -a, and -h options: detailed information, all files, and human-readable sizes.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ls -lt

    🔹 List files and folders with detailed information, sorted by modification time. The most recently modified file will be displayed first.
